30
Real-Life Example

Using Java is like driving an automatic car instead of a manual car. Many difficult operations are handled automatically.

4. Object-Oriented
Definition

Java is based on Object-Oriented Programming (OOP).

Everything in Java is organized using classes and objects.

OOP Concepts
Class
Object
Inheritance
Polymorphism
Abstraction
Encapsulation
Example
class Student {

    String name = "Om";

}

public class Demo {

