--------------------------------------------------------------

public

Accessible from anywhere.

--------------------------------------------------

static

Can be called without creating an object.

--------------------------------------------------

void

Returns nothing.

--------------------------------------------------

main

Name of the method.

--------------------------------------------------

String[] args

Stores command-line arguments.

--------------------------------------------------------------
10. Statements
--------------------------------------------------------------

Definition:

Instructions written inside main() are called statements.

Example:

System.out.println("Hello");

int a = 10;

int b = 20;

System.out.println(a+b);

--------------------------------------------------------------
11. Comments in Java
--------------------------------------------------------------

Comments are ignored by the compiler.

They are used to explain the code.

--------------------------------------------------------------
12. Single Line Comment
--------------------------------------------------------------

Syntax:

// This is a comment

