                 JAVA NOTES - VARIABLES IN JAVA
==============================================================

Topic No: 5

--------------------------------------------------------------
1. Introduction
--------------------------------------------------------------

A variable is a named memory location used to store data.

The value stored in a variable can change during program
execution.

Variables make it possible to store numbers, characters,
strings, decimal values, and other types of data.

--------------------------------------------------------------
2. Definition
--------------------------------------------------------------

A variable is a container that stores data in memory.

Example:

int age = 21;

Here,

Variable Name : age

Value         : 21

Data Type     : int

--------------------------------------------------------------
3. Real-Life Example
--------------------------------------------------------------

Think of a variable as a water bottle.

Bottle Name  → Variable Name

Water Inside → Value

Bottle Size  → Data Type

You can change the water inside the bottle whenever needed,
just as you can change the value of a variable.

--------------------------------------------------------------
4. Syntax
--------------------------------------------------------------

dataType variableName = value;

Example:

int age = 20;

double salary = 45000.50;

char grade = 'A';

String name = "Om";

--------------------------------------------------------------
5. Declaring a Variable
--------------------------------------------------------------

Declaration means creating a variable.

Example:

int number;

String city;

double price;

--------------------------------------------------------------
6. Initialization
--------------------------------------------------------------

Initialization means assigning a value to a variable.

Example:

int number = 100;

String city = "Nashik";

double price = 45.75;

--------------------------------------------------------------
7. Declaration and Initialization Separately
--------------------------------------------------------------

int age;

age = 22;

--------------------------------------------------------------
8. Memory Representation
--------------------------------------------------------------

int age = 25;

 -------------------------
| Variable | Value        |
|----------|--------------|
| age      | 25           |
 -------------------------

Memory stores the value 25 and the variable name "age"
refers to that memory location.

--------------------------------------------------------------
