==============================================================
                 JAVA NOTES - LOOPS IN JAVA
==============================================================

TOPIC NO: 8

==============================================================
1. INTRODUCTION
==============================================================

In Java, when we want to execute a block of code repeatedly,
we use LOOPS.

Without loops:
We must write same code again and again.

With loops:
We write code once and repeat automatically.

Example:
Printing numbers 1 to 100

==============================================================
2. DEFINITION
==============================================================

A loop is a control statement that executes a block of code
multiple times based on a condition.

==============================================================
3. TYPES OF LOOPS IN JAVA
==============================================================

1. for loop
2. while loop
3. do-while loop

==============================================================
4. FOR LOOP
==============================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------
Definition:
--------------------------------------------------------------
for loop is used when number of iterations is known.

--------------------------------------------------------------
Syntax:
--------------------------------------------------------------
for(initialization; condition; increment/decrement) {
    // code
}

--------------------------------------------------------------
Example:
--------------------------------------------------------------
for(int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    System.out.println(i);
}

--------------------------------------------------------------
Output:
--------------------------------------------------------------
1
2
3
4
5

==============================================================
5. FOR LOOP FLOW
==============================================================

1. Initialization (i = 1)
2. Condition check (i <= 5)
3. Execute code
4. Increment (i++)
5. Repeat until condition false

==============================================================
6. WHILE LOOP
==============================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------
Definition:
--------------------------------------------------------------
while loop is used when number of iterations is NOT fixed.

--------------------------------------------------------------
Syntax:
--------------------------------------------------------------
while(condition) {
    // code
    increment/decrement;
}

--------------------------------------------------------------
Example:
--------------------------------------------------------------
int i = 1;

while(i <= 5) {
    System.out.println(i);
    i++;
}

--------------------------------------------------------------
Output:
--------------------------------------------------------------
1
2
3
4
5

==============================================================
7. WHILE LOOP FLOW
==============================================================

1. Condition check
2. If true → execute block
3. Update variable
4. Repeat
5. Stop when false

==============================================================
8. DO-WHILE LOOP
==============================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------
Definition:
--------------------------------------------------------------
do-while loop executes at least ONCE,
even if condition is false.

--------------------------------------------------------------
Syntax:
--------------------------------------------------------------
do {
    // code
} while(condition);

--------------------------------------------------------------
Example:
--------------------------------------------------------------
int i = 1;

do {
    System.out.println(i);
    i++;
} while(i <= 5);

--------------------------------------------------------------
Output:
--------------------------------------------------------------
1
2
3
4
5

==============================================================
9. DO-WHILE SPECIAL CASE
==============================================================

Example:
int i = 10;

do {
    System.out.println(i);
} while(i <= 5);

Output:
10

(Executed once even though condition is false)

==============================================================
10. DIFFERENCE BETWEEN LOOPS
==============================================================

FOR LOOP:
- Fixed iterations
- Best when count is known

WHILE LOOP:
- Condition based
- Count not known

DO-WHILE:
- Executes at least once

==============================================================
11. NESTED LOOP
==============================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------
Definition:
--------------------------------------------------------------
A loop inside another loop.

--------------------------------------------------------------
Example:
--------------------------------------------------------------
for(int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
    for(int j = 1; j <= 2; j++) {
        System.out.println(i + " " + j);
    }
}

--------------------------------------------------------------
Output:
--------------------------------------------------------------
1 1
1 2
2 1
2 2
3 1
3 2

==============================================================
12. COMMON USES OF LOOPS
==============================================================

- Number printing
- Pattern printing
- Array traversal
- Sum of numbers
- Factorial
- Fibonacci series

==============================================================
13. COMMON MISTAKES
==============================================================

❌ Infinite loop

while(true) { }

----------------------------------------------

❌ Missing increment

while(i <= 5) {
    System.out.println(i);
}

✔ Fix:
i++;

----------------------------------------------

❌ Wrong condition

for(i = 1; i < 5; i--)  ❌

