(RAM), but data is lost when program stops.

To store data permanently, we use FILE HANDLING.

Example:
- Saving student records
- Bank transaction history
- Login data
- Reports

==============================================================
2. DEFINITION
==============================================================

File Handling in Java is a mechanism to store, read, and
modify data in files using Java programs.

